      "author_association" : "CONTRIBUTOR",
      "body" : "Yes it should be updated as its confusing at this moment. Incoming i2p connections work by default if i2psam is set with i2p working correctly. Maybe we could change this to:\r\n\r\n```\r\n     Incoming I2P connections are accepted via the SAM proxy\r\n     by default. If this is set to 0 and -i2psam is set\r\n     then only outgoing connections will be made to the I2P network.\r\n     Ignored if -i2psam is not set. Listening for incoming I2P\r\n     connections is done through the SAM proxy, not by binding to a\r\n     local address and port (default: 1)\r\n     \r\n```",
      "commit_id" : "92f43b479a9673f5475d0de9c731b9f7a37a1c86",
      "created_at" : "2023-01-07T02:52:00Z",
